<id>http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=6525&amp;p=28491#p28491</id>
<link href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=6525&amp;p=28491#p28491"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: Hide/rename Apps]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=6525&amp;p=28491#p28491"><![CDATA[
Right click on any app and choose &quot;Create shortcut&quot;. Allow Windows to create a shortcut to the app on the Desktop. You can cut and paste all these shortcuts into one folder, rename them as you want. Then go to Customize Start Menu tab. Double click the &quot;Apps&quot; item and remove everything from the &quot;Command&quot; field. Then type or copy-paste the path to the folder of shortcuts you created in the &quot;Link&quot; field of the Apps item. Voila, you have a new apps folder with only the apps you use and the rest hidden.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=54">Gaurav</a> — Wed Aug 10, 2016 10:41 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
</entry>
